# Vite + React client

## Router
- React Router drives `/`, `/login`, `/auth/callback`, `/onboarding`, `/dashboard`.
- `App.tsx` registers routes; feature `pages/*` hold screen components.

## Supabase in the browser
- `createClient()` in `client/src/shared/lib/supabase.ts` uses `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` and `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`.
- Used **only for auth** (`supabase.auth.*`) and to fetch the access token for `Authorization: Bearer ...`. Never call `supabase.from(...)` from the client.
- Session: `@supabase/supabase-js` default storage (localStorage). No Next middleware — use `RequireAuth` + `onAuthStateChange` where needed.

## Server API
- All data IO goes through `client/src/shared/lib/api.ts` (which posts to `${VITE_SERVER_URL}`). It attaches the bearer token, surfaces typed `ApiError`, and uses DTOs from `@wedding-hall/shared`.

## Auth callback
- `exchangeCodeForSession` runs in `AuthCallbackPage` after email/magic-link redirects, then calls `upsertProfile()` against the server.

## Env
- Only `VITE_*` vars are exposed to the client bundle. Required: `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, `VITE_SERVER_URL`.

## Build
- `npm run build -w wedding-hall-client` (or `npm run build` from root).
